          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>a and b are <fr:strong>congruent modulo n</fr:strong>:</fr:p>
            <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a \equiv  b \quad  (mod \ n)]]></fr:tex>
            <fr:p>If <fr:strong>n divides b - a</fr:strong>, or if <fr:strong>b = a + nk</fr:strong> for some integer k This is an <fr:link type="local" href="equivalence%20relation.xml" addr="equivalence relation" title="Equivalence relation">equivalence relation</fr:link></fr:p>
            <fr:p>So we may consider the <fr:link type="local" href="equivalence%20class.xml" addr="equivalence class" title="Equivalence class">equivalence class</fr:link> -&gt; <fr:link type="local" href="congruence%20class.xml" addr="congruence class" title="Congruence class">congruence class</fr:link> modulo n (<fr:link type="local" href="residue%20class.xml" addr="residue class" title="Residue class">residue class</fr:link> modulo n)</fr:p>
            <fr:p>
              <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\bar {a} = \{\dots , a-2n, a-n, a, a+n, a+2n, \dots \}]]></fr:tex>
            </fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" expanded="false" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:anchor>479</fr:anchor>
