          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>A subdivision of S into nonoverlapping subsets:</fr:p>
            <fr:p>
              <fr:strong><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> =# union of disjoint, nonempty sets;</fr:strong>
            </fr:p>
            <fr:p>Example:</fr:p>
            <fr:ul><fr:li>Even integers and odd integers form a partition of the set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Z]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li>Sets <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[ {1,2} ]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[ {3,4} ]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[ {5} ]]></fr:tex> form a partition of the set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[ {1,2,3,4,5} ]]></fr:tex></fr:li></fr:ul>
            <fr:p>Logically equivalent to an <fr:link type="local" href="equivalence%20relation.xml" addr="equivalence relation" title="Equivalence relation">equivalence relation</fr:link></fr:p>
